Description:
Treasured Retreat with Loads of Potential!
If you're looking for an escape from the hustle and bustle, it doesn't get much better than this three bedroom, two bathroom sanctuary nestled at the foot of a tranquil bushland reserve!
Topping the list of families, renovators, and developers alike, this treasured home set on a sprawling over approximately half of an acre of land instantly charms with hardwood floors and timber-lined walls, a spacious living with a fireplace, dedicated dining, classy kitchen featuring a stainless steel splashback, dual sink, and quality appliances (incl. a 900 mm gas cooktop), family zone, private study, three well-sized bedrooms (two with BIRs), two modern bathrooms (both with separate bath and shower), private toilet, and laundry.
An enormous front yard and a generous back garden present a potential hard to match, to build further accommodation whether as a bigger family home, holiday retreat, or even a charming B&B (STCA). Additional highlights include a front balcony, ramp access to the residence, ducted heating, main gas plumbing, and 2 x garages/storage sheds (1 double, 1 single) with bitumen driveway access.
Wonderfully located with easy access to Cockatoo Reserve, Wright Forest Bushland Reserve, and Cockatoo train station; it is also close to Cockatoo Primary School and Emerald Secondary College.

Description:
'Daphne Manor' on 6 Acres!
If you are looking for a family home with country charm and enough cleared acres for a pony or three that is still close to Cockatoo Township and only a few minutes from Emerald, this is the place for you! Featuring a gorgeous, character filled home, which was once an old school house from the inner suburbs that was moved to the Hills for a new lease of life. The home features 3 bedrooms with built in robes, the Master with ensuite, walk in robe and the original fireplace and mantel for an old fashioned touch and there is a split system for modern comfort and convenience. Add to this the spacious, timber lined family bathroom with black claw foot bath and black and white checked tiles and a powder room with original cast toilet. The large kitchen has plenty of storage, an electric stove and a gas cook top as well as a wood fired Rayburn Stove, fantastic for cooking and heating. The best room of the house though would have to be the huge family room which is bathed in natural light, features pretty leadlight windows, has a wood heater for warmth and a split system for heating and cooling. This room flows onto the undercover entertaining deck, the perfect place to relax after a long day with a glass of wine or a cuppa and watch the sun set while taking in the elevated views over the property. Add to this a huge shed with 2 fully lined stables and high roof suitable for a hoist or high enough to fit the largest of vans or boats, a 4 car carport which provides undercover access to the home & is also high enough for floats, trucks or vans, a fully fenced and flood lit tennis court, a flood lit arena, pretty cottage gardens with an abundance of roses and two driveway access. Altogether there are 4 paddocks with water & 2 yards, a dam and a variety of trees including apples, nashi apples, pears, plums and lemons. There is also a separate cottage on the property that is privately located from the home and overlooks the tennis court and paddocks, ideal for teenagers, guests or in-law accommodation. Houses of this style and acreage of this size have become a rarity book an inspection today and prepare to fall in love!
CALL SAMANTHA ON 0438 680 032 TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!

Description:
Fresh and New With Nothing To Do!
If you're looking for a fresh start for the family, look no further. This contemporary styled home is new, fresh and immaculately presented as well as being perfectly positioned within walking distance to Cockatoo Township, public transport, shops and cafes. The home offers 4 bedrooms, 3 with built in robes, the Master with walk in robe and ensuite, huge family living room, dining area and wonderful sparkling kitchen. The kitchen cupboards are gleaming white offset with stone look bench tops, stainless appliances and tiled splash back with fresh green accents, add to this a large walk in pantry and its the entertainers dream. One of the first things you'll notice when you walk into this home is the soaring 10ft ceilings giving the home a light airy feel. Other features include lots of natural light, quality carpets, floorboards, mains gas ducted heating and split system cooling so the home is comfortable all year round. Vehicles are covered with a double carport at the front and a double garage/workshop out the back. The property is securely fenced for safety with a large cleared lawn area and has mains water and sewer connected making it a truly low maintenance hills home.

Description:
PEACE AND SOLITUDE ON JUST UNDER AN ACRE
Located in a peaceful pocket of Cockatoo is this quaint character cottage surrounded by nature, perfect for a first home buyer or someone looking for a quiet secluded retreat.
Sitting on 1 acre approx. this home offers two bedrooms, first with built in wardrobe, the second bedroom could also be a well-lit living area, older styled kitchen, lounge and bathroom. An old shed stands beside the home with a seasonal creek surrounded with tree ferns running along a gully.
This private and peaceful block is in a great location in a town recently ranked as number three most family-friendly suburb and as the second best suburb for property investment in Victoria, Cockatoo has a lot to offer the astute buyer. Plenty of options for schooling, walking distance to sporting facilities and so much more to offer a growing family and a tree-change lifestyle close to the growing number of shops and services in Cockatoo's McBride Street where a brand new IGA development is currently underway.

Description:
Well Located & Low Maintenance!
This is the ideal first home for young families, or downsizers. Immaculate inside and out the brick family home is perfectly located within walking distance to Cockatoo township and all it has to offer. You can walk the kids to school, do the shopping, walk to the bus stop or just wander into town for your weekend breaky at the local cafe. The home offers space and comfort with 3 bedrooms with built in robes, the Master with walk in robe and ensuite. Add to this a formal lounge to the front for relaxing in and at the back of the house the living meals and kitchen are open plan and family friendly with access to the undercover entertaining area. The kitchen is spotless with gas cooktop, dishwasher, large pantry and breakfast bench. The home is kept warm and cosy in the cooler months with mains gas ducted heating and has low maintenance flooring throughout with as new carpet in the bedrooms and lounge room. Outside is a delight for those who like to grow their own vegies with covered vegie patch and there are fruit trees, roses and clipped hedges front and back for structure. For the man of the house there is a large shed/workshop or perhaps extra car storage as well as a double lockup garage at the front of the home. As there is really nothing to do here, this home will free up your time to do the things you enjoy.

Description:
Magnificent
This is a once in a life time opportunity to buy the home of your dreams. This magnificent American Ranch style home is reminiscent of the television show Dallas with the impressive stone entrance and automatic gates opening onto the newly concreted driveway which winds down stone edged manicured garden beds to the circular driveway complete with 3 tiered fountain. The home's facade gives a hint of whats behind but once inside you will be enamored with the grand proportions. Step inside and you'll be greeted with the gorgeous entertainers kitchen with granite featured on all the bench tops (including the butlers pantry), there is stunning cabinetry with glass display cupboards, huge 1200mm stainless oven with gas cooktop and for convenience the kitchen is accessed from the double garage (with remote doors), so you will never be caught in the rain. Opposite the kitchen is the dining room with glamorous chandelier, then the theatre room or perhaps a formal lounge.
The grand staircase is located in the middle of the home with the stairs stretching out to both sides of the bedroom level. As you would expect the Master has a large walk in robe and ensuite with double vanity and spa bath, the further 4 bedrooms are large and all have built in robes. Back downstairs you'll find open plan living cleverly designed with a wall dividing the games room from the family room which has a stunning stone feature wall with ambient wood heater for wintery nights. This area has towering pitched ceilings with timber beams for a rustic lodge feel and leads out to the wrap around timber deck. Add to this a Bar Room complete with plumbing and powder room. From here you'll find the study/home office with external access and there's also a cellar for all your expensive wines or treasures!
No expense has been spared with fixtures and fittings and features including spotted gum & iron-bark floors, double glazed windows, hydronic gas heating, split system cooling and ducted vacuum.
Outside the grand proportions continue with the huge (25x10) shed incorporating a 1 bedroom loft style apartment, perfect for extended family/visitors or perhaps a work from home studio. Add to this an enormous barn/wood shed with enough wood storage to keep you going for many cold winters, 100,000 litres of water, fenced paddocks if you have horses, a dam filed with water lilies with a decked bridge and rotunda, which is a peaceful place to relax and watch the gorgeous sunsets.
This is truly an amazing property and will be the envy of all your friends. Words are not enough to do this property justice organise your private inspection today!

Description:
The Perfect Package!
Get in quick for this great starter or investment situated a convenient quiet location! This home boasts a comfortable floor plan including lounge /dining room with nearby kitchen plus separate family room which opens out onto the rear deck. There are three bedrooms including a master with access to the central bathroom and built in robe. The block is a usable 1/4 of an acre with double carport and garden shed. Special features include gas ducted heating, under house storage and easy care gardens. For the investor the property is tenanted at $350 per week....what are you waiting for – inspect today! Mick Dolphin on 0429 684522, Meaghan Dolphin on 0422 578 114 or Amie Colbert on 0413 160 413 to arrange your inspection now.
Due to strong market conditions please call before the open to confirm that it is still going ahead.

Description:
FAMILY LIVING ON 1 ACRE
Set in a sought after location on approximately 1 acre is this well maintained property, featuring established gardens mature shrubs and trees. The cedar family home is spacious and offers a great country ambience with timber features throughout. A functional floorplan consists of 4 spacious bedrooms all with BIRs and cathedral ceilings, a large living area with a solid fuel heater, a light and bright timber kitchen that is both central and spacious, and a huge family bathroom. Extra features of the home are ducted gas heating, polished timber floors throughout and ceiling fans. Step outside to a huge garage that has an extra family/games room within, and also caters for extra car accommodation/workshop. With additional 2 car carport, chicken coop and excellent private gardens, this is a great family property!
Due to strong market conditions please call before the open to confirm that it is still going ahead.

Description:
Privately Located & Walk to Town on 3.2 Acres!
If quality, style and size are important this classic ranch style home of large proportions is the perfect home for you. Privately located, this brilliant family home provides the space needed with separate living spaces so Mum and Dad can get a little alone time and the kids have plenty of room to have their friends over. Recently renovated the home consists of 4 great sized bedrooms with built in robes, Master with ensuite, stylish family bathroom, powder room, beautiful kitchen with lots of clever storage, a family room and formal lounge room. The home has ambient features such as a wood heater in the dining area and open fireplaces in the family and lounge rooms which are set into rendered walls painted in warm tones, perfect for family and friends to gather around on chilly winter nights for fun and laughter. For convenience there is mains gas ducted heating. For entertaining the undercover deck has a built in spa and overlooks the property, including the dam filled with water lilies. Storage is taken care of with under house storage and a double remote garage with concreted floor and water connected so you can wash up before going inside. You'll love the asphalt drive and the gardens which flow naturally and are low maintenance; in fact there is nothing to do here except move in and enjoy living. Inspection is a must as words and photos do not do this home justice.
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!
Stephen Richards 0400 100 155

Description:
"Bibbenluke" Simply Stunning!
Privately located on a flat usable 3/4 acre block, this family home has absolutely everything done for you. The attractive brick home has been masterfully updated inside and out with style that sparkles, comprising of 4 bedrooms, the Master with huge dressing room and a stylish ensuite with fully tiled double shower with massage jets. Add to this a huge living room and separate family room and the large kitchen/dining. No expense has been spared in this kitchen with beautiful granite bench tops, plenty of cupboards and draws, huge pantry and 1100 freestanding stove with gas cooktop and 2 x 500mm ovens underneath, perfect for the chef who loves to entertain. The home's features include high ceilings with decorative cornices, hardwood floors, mains gas ducted heating, powder room, mains water and two fabulous outdoor paved entertaining areas. For vehicles you have double gates leading to a double lock up garage with ample parking towards the rear. The lovely gardens are established with numerous fruit and specimen trees, lots of lush lawn area for the kids or furry friends and the property is fully fenced for safety. Given the style and location of the home it will not be on the market long so be quick to book your private inspection, you'll love it!
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!
Grant Day 0417 565 745 or Bethany Day 0438 844 968

Description:
Potential For So Much More!
This 3 bedroom home on over half a usable acre represents a fantastic opportunity to buy into the popular hills town of Cockatoo with plenty of room to extend (STCA) or improve to your own taste. Well located with dual access and private being the only house in the street! Offering the 3 bedrooms with built in robes, the Master with ensuite, light filled kitchen and dining area opening out to the outdoor entertaining, large lounge with toasty wood heater, family bathroom and laundry. Features of the home include lovely polished floorboards, cathedral pitched ceiling, mains gas ducted heating, split system cooling and mains water. Outside you'll love the huge open sunny rear yard with established tree hedge for privacy, paved entertaining area, garden shed and the front yard is cleared ready for planting your dream garden. This home is bound to be popular with first home buyers and investors alike so be quick to arrange your inspection today.

Description:
Country Lifestyle Modern Living
With a breath-taking home of some 34 squares (approx.) Designed and built by Country Lane Home this property has an instant attraction and lasting appeal that affords you the lifestyle you've been dreaming of. With immaculate presentation and stunning features you need only move in and relax, enjoy and unwind in a home that is pure bliss in a highly prized position. Designed with a family in mind, the superb property sits on 3065 m2 (approx) (yes - over 3/4 of an acre) and utilities smart choices in the well planned use of space which allows upstairs and downstairs living.
The heart of the home is the open plan family room adjacent to the enormous designer kitchen with stone benches, stainless steel appliances, 900mm oven with glass splash backs. Move outside to an alfresco that dreams are made of - blurring the lines between indoor and outdoor living spaces effortlessly, you will enjoy entertaining your friends and family on the extensive timber deck with overlooking the treetops. The kids will love the space to play out in the back yard - hours of entertainment for sure!
5 bedrooms, the master of king size proportions on the top floor with its own private balcony, his and hers walk in robe's and ensuite of grand scale. Separate your space from the children's rooms that are located down stairs accompanied by a second living area. All feature built in robes and are serviced by a family bathroom.
Features include 2 large split systems, polished hardwood floors & porcelain tiles, stone bench tops, built in storage cupboards in the 2.5 car garage, side access for trailers and boats with a site cut for a huge shed.
The home is all class in a highly sort after position - don't miss this extraordinary chance to live the country lifestyle Dream.

Description:
THE TREE CHANGE YOU HAVE BEEN WAITING FOR WITH THE LOCATION AND LIFESTYLE
Set amongst the beautiful forestry of the Dandenong Ranges is this established four bedroom home, awaiting it new owners to enjoy.
The residence has been freshly painted throughout and will not disappoint with the Master bedroom featuring a his and her double BIR, ensuite with oversized shower and its own private garden courtyard, making it the perfect place for your morning coffee with the birds.
Bedrooms 2,3 and 4 are located to the rear of the home and all feature their own hydronic heating units plus beds 2 and 4 feature double built n robes.
The newly renovated kitchen includes electric oven, gas cook-top, dishwasher and overlooks the open plan family and dining area which is bright and airy making it the perfect place for the family to congregate.
The formal living features a gas fireplace and is set at the front of the house which means there is an abundance of space for the whole family to enjoy.
Outside is where you will find the spacious undercover entertaining area with the forest surroundings at your feet plus an abundance of space 1 ¼ acres (approx) for the kids to play and enjoy.
There is a double carport, workman's shed with shelving, work bench and power, an open storage area off the carport along with an exceptional amount of off street parking.
The property is 2 minutes' drive to the Cockatoo Township, close to the local Primary School, Wright Forrest and public transport but the privacy & tranquillity makes it seem miles away from everything.
